The '''Ingalalla Waterfalls''' is  a [[Waterfall#Types|cascade waterfall]] in the  Australian state of [[South Australia]] located in the locality of [[Hay Flat, South Australia|Hay Flat]] on an unnamed creek on the [[Fleurieu Peninsula]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ingalalla Waterfalls|url=http://www.yankalilla.sa.gov.au/page.aspx?u=381&t=uList&ulistId=0&c=4270|publisher=District Council of Yankalilla|accessdate=15 July 2015}}</ref><ref name=PLB/>

The waterfall is situated approximately {{convert|8.3|km}} south of the town of {{SAcity|Yankalilla}} and {{convert|70|km}} south southwest of the state capital of [[Adelaide city centre|Adelaide]], the waterfalls descend from an elevation of {{convert|253|m}} [[Australian Height Datum|above sea level]] in the range of {{Convert|81|-|92|m}} to the [[Second Valley]] below.<ref name=bonzle/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/flash-flood-ordeal-over-for-aberfoyle-park-family/story-e6freo8c-1225748683897|title=Flash flood ordeal over for Aberfoyle Park family|author1=Noonan, Amy|author2=Wills, Daniel|work=[[The Advertiser (Adelaide)|The Advertiser]]|location=Adelaide|date=12 July 2009|accessdate=31 May 2014 }}</ref>

Its name was approved on 25 May 2000 in response to "a request for clarification from the [[Royal Automobile Association of South Australia|Royal Automobile Association]] on which name to use for the feature."<ref name = PLB/>

